cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.ST, cs.IT, cs.SY 

The paper proposes a model-based framework for uncertainty quantification in statistical machine learning. It discusses the application of the framework to linear models, Poisson processes, and deep neural networks for classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the hierarchical modeling perspective, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also discusses the computational scalability and robustness to outliers, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
